A gas leak on the Snorre A platform in the North Sea led to the evacuation of workers and a significant loss in oil output.
Statoil, the operator, faced challenges in resuming production due to safety concerns and adverse weather conditions.
The incident impacted Norway's oil exports, highlighting the importance of safety measures in offshore operations.
Despite efforts to seal the well and resume production, uncertainties remain regarding the timeline for full recovery.
The Norwegian Petroleum Safety Authority plays a crucial role in overseeing safety protocols to prevent future incidents in the offshore oil industry.
